{"title":"Bubblegum Aliens","link":"https://kottke.org/24/05/bubblegum-aliens","date":1714595045000,"content":"\n        <p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/C6HysTNucSq/\">These</a> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/C6PcY5ZOiPk/\">bubblegum</a> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/C6RIwKUuSOq/\">sculptures</a> created and photographed by artist <a href=\"https://www.hisuzanne.com/\">Suzanne Saroff</a> are <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/C6W3wMUu_E7/\">delightfully disgusting</a>.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/saroff-gum-01.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/saroff-gum-01.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/saroff-gum-01.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1625\" alt=\"half-popped bubblegum that looks like mangled flesh\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/saroff-gum-02.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/saroff-gum-02.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/saroff-gum-02.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1625\" alt=\"bubblegum scultpure that looks like an alien\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/saroff-gum-03.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/saroff-gum-03.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/saroff-gum-03.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1625\" alt=\"unpopped bubblegum bubble that has saliva all over it, gross\" /></p>\n\n<p>I found this <a href=\"https://www.thisiscolossal.com/2024/04/suzanne-saroff-bubblegum/\">via Grace Ebert at Colossal</a>, who writes:</p>\n\n<blockquote><p>Conjuring memories of childhood competitions and absent-minded chomping, the photos zoom in on chewed wads of pink, blue, and green that appear almost corporeal, their pudgy folds and pockets evoking the beauty and repulsion of the human body.</p></blockquote>\n\n<p>I love these but grrrrossssss. (And I donâ€™t know why, but these remind me of <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/B4xWH4bhEDy/?hl=en\">Roe Ethridgeâ€™s photo of Andrew W.K.</a>)</p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/art\">art</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Suzanne%20Saroff\">Suzanne Saroff</a></p>\n\n         <p>ðŸ’¬ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/24/05/bubblegum-aliens\">Join the discussion on kottke.org</a> â†’</p>\n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"e1e8d4fb641c941d1e970e3f01435921a35a96567e38c01f1ae9ec9e6103e47e","category":"default"}